<% layout('layouts/main') -%>
<section class="container py-5">
  <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-lg-10">
      <div class="card shadow-sm border-0">
        <div class="card-body p-4 p-lg-5">
          <h1 class="h2 fw-semibold text-dark mb-4">Cookie Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-secondary">Last updated: July 5, 2026</p>
          <hr class="my-4">
          <p class="text-secondary">RaiseTool uses cookies to improve user experience, maintain temporary session stability, and safeguard analytics. This document explains what cookies we use, why we use them, and your choices regarding cookies.</p>
          
          <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold text-dark mt-4 mb-3">1. What are Cookies?</h2>
          <p class="text-secondary">Cookies are small text files stored on your browser or device by web servers. They help websites remember information about your visit to streamline navigation and keep configurations persistent.</p>
          
          <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold text-dark mt-4 mb-3">2. How RaiseTool Uses Cookies</h2>
          <p class="text-secondary">We strictly use cookies for essential utility routing and anonymous tracking. The cookies used are categorized as follows:</p>
          <ul class="text-secondary small">
            <li><strong>Essential Session Cookies:</strong> We utilize encrypted, signed cookies containing cryptographic session IDs to link your client session to your temporary workspace context. This is required to process files and prevent security session hijacking. These cookies expire after 10 minutes of inactivity.</li>
            <li><strong>Security Tokens (CSRF):</strong> Safe verification tokens are stored to prevent cross-site request forgery attacks on action forms.</li>
            <li><strong>Theme Preference:</strong> We store your dark/light theme choice (<code>theme</code>) in <code>localStorage</code> (a client-side cookie equivalent) to persist your workspace UI selection.</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold text-dark mt-4 mb-3">3. Managing and Deleting Cookies</h2>
          <p class="text-secondary">Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings preferences. If you disable cookies, please note that you will not be able to utilize active workspaces or run multi-step server processing workflows. You can clear your temporary session cookies at any time by deleting cookies inside your browser settings or by clearing your workspace assets.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
